Package ru.tinkoff.qa.neptune.selenium.api.widget

Annotation Interface Priority

@Retention(RUNTIME) @Target(TYPE) public @interface Priority
This annotation is used to define a priority of widgets to find. It is useful when some subclass of the Widget has few child classes and it is necessary to define which classes are supposed to be instantiated first.

    • value

      int value
      Defines the priority of similar widgets for the searching. The lower number means the higher priority. The value to be set should be between 1 and Integer.MAX_VALUE
      Returns:
      the number of priority of the searching for widget.
